               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. SCRIVBN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">CLERK</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1282" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1282" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1282" type="surname" value="SEDGWICK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1282" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD SEDGWICK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a publican. On 24th March I saw the pri<lb></lb>soners at my house—they had some gin—Mallyon paid for it with a shilling—I gave it to my son—I saw him give change, and place the shilling in the till.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1283" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1283" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1283" type="surname" value="SEDGWICK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1283" type="given" value="CHARLES FREDERICK"></interp>CHARLES FREDERICK SEDGWICK</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoners at my father's—Mallyon laid a shilling down—rny father drew it across the counter, and gave it me—I put it into the till—there were three 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. pieces there, but no other</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184904090212"></xptr>
               <p>shilling—when the officer came, I took the shilling out and gave it him there had been no other shilling put into the till.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1284" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1284" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1284" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1284" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS RICHARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pork-butcher. On 24th March Mallyon came to my shop for half a pig's head; he gave me a half-crown, I gave him 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. change—I laid the half-crown on the counter while I entered the meat, and while it laid there a policeman came in—I crossed the half-crown, and gave it to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1285" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1285" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1285" type="surname" value="WHITLAMB"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1285" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WHITLAMB</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, M</hi> 89). On 24th March I saw the prisoners standing conversing together—I saw something pass from Jenkins to Mallyon, and they both went into Mr. Sedgwick's—they came out—I went in and received this shilling from his son, who bent it, and the father marked it—I came out, and then saw Mallyon go into Richards' shop—he came out with a pig's head—I went in, and received this half-crown from Biggs.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Jenkins. Q.</hi> How far were you off when you saw us talking together? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> A dozen yards—I had seen your features before you got there, from the light of a lamp. <hi rend="smallCaps">CALEB EDWARD POWELL</hi>. This shilling and half-crown are both counterfeit, <hi rend="italic">Mallyon's Defence.</hi> I made a trunk for Jenkins on the Saturday following; I met him, and he paid me 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for it, which the officers saw pass; we went and had some gin; I gave a shilling, and we came out; I saw no more of him till Monday morning.</p>
